data.name: biHomeServerStatus.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Turn on the ability to receive files directly from other Prometheus users through the Direct Transfer feature.

The server is currently disabled.
Enabling the server will allow outside access to port 31337. Any time you open a port on your computer there is a minor security risk.

It is recommended that you configure your firewall to only allow Prometheus access to this port, configure the server settings, and only enable the server when you are expecting a file.

data.name: liLightingRadiosityTmo.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Set the tone mapping operator to use when running radiosity.

A tone mapping is a technique used to approximate the appearance of high dynamic range images in media with a more limited dynamic range. CRT and LCD monitors, as well as projectors, have a very limited dynamic range.

Tone mapping helps to address the problem of strong contrast reduction from the scene values (radiance) to the displayable range while preserving the image details and color appearance important to appreciate the original scene content.

For more information on tone mapping, see this article.

data.value:
Toggle yaw randomization in the active project. When an object is created, its yaw rotational value will be randomly assigned if this option is enabled.
Yaw pivots an object to face left or right, rotating it on the Z-axis.

data.name: biScriptingFormatRegion.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Toggle selected text between being enclosed in a region and not being enclosed in a region.

A region will be removed when selecting only an existing region, from #region to #endregion.

A region will be added when selecting any other text, even if the text includes other regions within it.

data.name: biScriptingFormatComment.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Toggle selected text between being commented out and being active code.

Comments will be removed when the selected text contains only comments and whitespace.

A comment will be created when selecting any other text, even if the text includes other comments within it.

data.name: biTagsImportDataSound.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Create a new sound tag from an audio file.

Click the arrow to pre-select sound encoding options before being taken to the import dialog.

By Codec - Choose a codec and set its options manually. This method provides the most control over encoding.

By Type - Choose the type of sound the audio file is and the encoding options will be automatically set for the best fit.

data.name: biFileMenuLaunch.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Create, access, and import projects, tags, and scripts, store or close open documents and distribute tags and scripts to other Prometheus users.
Quickly access recent projects and tags through their respective lists.
Modify Prometheus options or exit the application.
